The reason I have come for a sight test today is because I've noticed my distance vision is no longer as good as it was, and I don't have any glasses for my distance vision. I do however wear glasses for reading. I've been wearing reading glasses for the past 15 years and I can see well with them. I'm not really having any other visual problems but I do get headaches occasionally.

 I don't wear contact lenses.

I'm not really having any other visual problems but I do get headaches occasionally.

 I don't wear contact lenses.

 My last eye test was on 26/10/2019, but I think my reading glasses are a little older, I can't quite remember.

 For the past year now I've been getting dull headaches, on and off, on the side of my head, around once a week, when doing computer work or reading for long periods of time. Luckily, I don't get any eyestrain but the headaches are getting annoying.

 I don't get any double vision or floaters but for several years I've been getting flashes in my vision every night, not sure if its happening in both eyes or just one. Other than that I haven't noticed anything else. I don't get any floating things in my vision.

Other than that I haven't noticed anything else. I don't get any floating things in my vision. I don't experience any pain or itching with my eyes but sometimes they feel dry and they are a bit red. My eyes were not patched when I was a child. 

 30 years ago I was discharged from the hospital after having cyst removal surgery and being prescribed lid scrubs for my blepharitis, that was the only time I went to the eye hospital.

 30 years ago I was discharged from the hospital after having cyst removal surgery and being prescribed lid scrubs for my blepharitis, that was the only time I went to the eye hospital. It was an eye opening experience. 

 My family don't have any eye or health problems. No one in my family has health problems such as diabetes or high blood pressure.

My family don't have any eye or health problems. No one in my family has health problems such as diabetes or high blood pressure. My dad did have cataracts. 

 My general health is good. I don't have diabetes but I am genetically predisposed to type 2 diabetes, and my last medical exam was 2 months ago to get my blood sugar levels checked.

I take vitamin D and cod liver oil supplements but do not take any medication, pills or tablets. Around May time I may take antihistamines and sometimes steroid drops if my hayfever really flares up. I don't smoke since I know it's damaging to my health.

 I work (occupation) as a teacher in a local secondary school. Its rewarding working as a teacher but it can be hard work too. 

 I spend about 6 hours a day looking at my computer screen.

 I spend about 6 hours a day looking at my computer screen. Its too long really and I wonder if that is contributing to my headaches.

 I drive to work most days in the car but occasionally I go on my motorbike.

 I drive to work most days in the car but occasionally I go on my motorbike. Its more fun going by motorbike but no so great when its raining. My motorbike is a KTM SMT 990, its a bit of a handful and makes me feel like a bit of a hooligan sometimes. 

 My main hobbies are motorcycling and climbing on the weekends.
